Package: curveRbayes
Title: Bayesian Immunoassay Standard Curve Fitting
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hardik", "Gupta",
           email = "Hardik.Gupta@dartmouth.edu",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Michael Scot", "Zens",
           email = "michael.s.zens@dartmouth.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Anne G.", "Hoen",
           email = "anne.g.hoen@dartmouth.edu",
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: Bayesian hierarchical standard curve fitting for immunoassay
    data. Fits logistic, Gompertz, and Richards models across multiple
    curve_ids using Stan, with data-adaptive priors, robust Student-t
    likelihood, LOO-CV model selection, and posterior predictive
    concentration estimation with full uncertainty propagation.
    Receives preprocessed data from curveRcore and produces
    calibration_result objects directly comparable to curveRfreq output.
URL: https://github.com/immunoplex/curveRbayes, https://immunoplex.github.io/curveRbayes
